Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.15,0:13:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- 贝莉特 主管的是 - 终于\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- ...Berit, who's in charge...- Finally!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.20,0:13:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 伯格曼周 - 在发了这么多邮件之后\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- ...of the Bergman Week.- After all the emails.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.66,0:13:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他说分钱比分房子简单多了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He said it would be easier to divide up money than homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.83,0:13:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,九个孩子\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Nine children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.37,0:13:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- 九个 - 九个\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Nine!- Nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.83,0:13:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- 来自六个不同的女人 - 哇哦\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- From six different women.- Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.38,0:13:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他不觉得困扰吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Didn't it bother him
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.38,0:13:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,要把一切都卖给陌生人\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}that everything would be sold to strangers?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.42,0:13:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,他不是伤春悲秋的人\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He wasn't sentimental.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.09,0:13:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他活在当下\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He lived in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.43,0:13:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,他相信上帝吗 我是说\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Did he believe in God?I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.97,0:13:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,这个问题很复杂 我肯定 但他有谈过吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}it was complicated, I'm sure,but did he ever talk about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.01,0:13:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他总说人死如灯灭\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He always said that death was just a light going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.27,0:13:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这在英格丽死后就变了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}That changed after Ingrid died.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼比什么都相信鬼魂\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Bergman believed in ghosts more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.82,0:13:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,当你孤身一人生活在僻远的小岛上 你懂的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}When you live alone on a remote island, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.40,0:13:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他能在屋里感受到英格丽的存在\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He felt Ingrid's presence in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.40,0:13:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他说她就在屋里\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He said she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.86,0:13:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,确信无疑\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He was absolutely convinced of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.57,0:13:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我在里面给你们准备了个座位 - 谢谢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- I have a table ready for you inside now.- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.58,0:13:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,就在吧台旁边\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's right here by the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.64,0:14:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他跟孩子们的关系怎么样\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}How was his relationship with his children?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.47,0:14:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,孩子小的时候 他们不怎么见面\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He didn't see much of them when they were young.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.94,0:14:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,说好听点 他不是一个看家的人 \N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He wasn't much of a family man, to put it mildly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.69,0:14:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,很多年来 他的一个女儿\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}For years, one of his daughters
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.52,0:14:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,都不知道他是她的父亲\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}didn't even know he was her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.57,0:14:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你们可以落座了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You can sit down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.40,0:14:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在他六十岁生日的时候有一场大团圆\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Then there was a big reunion at his 60th birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.11,0:14:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,英格丽说服了他把所有人邀请来\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Ingrid had persuaded him to invite everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.78,0:14:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,她很固执\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Ingrid was adamant about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.83,0:14:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,在修复伯格曼和他家庭的关系上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}reconstructing Bergman's relationship with his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.92,0:14:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 你觉得\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, do you think
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.84,0:14:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以在创作出这么多作品的同时\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}you can create a great body of work
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.55,0:14:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,也照看好家庭吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}and raise a family at the same time?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.80,0:14:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这么大体量的作品吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}A body of work of that scope?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.68,0:14:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,在42岁的时候 伯格曼已经指导了25部电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}At the age of 42, Bergman had directed 25 films,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.43,0:14:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,运营一家剧院 组织了多场话剧\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}run a theater, staged many plays.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.64,0:14:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得他该怎么做到这些\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}How do you think he would he have done that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.44,0:15:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他还要忙着换尿布的话\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}if he was also changing diapers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.02,0:15:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你觉得呢 - 实际一点说\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- How do you feel about that?- In practical terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.69,0:15:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,抚养九个孩子 拍五十部电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}raising nine kids, directing 50 films,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.94,0:15:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,更不用说还有那些戏剧 是有点苛求了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}not to mention the plays, seems like a tall order.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.95,0:15:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,对 但不实际地说\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, but in non-practical terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.12,0:15:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,母亲们抚养了全部九个孩子 他一点事没做\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}the mothers raised all the nine kids and he didn't do a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.91,0:15:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么想呢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}How do you feel about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.41,0:15:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我应该觉得糟糕 对吧 - 不\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- I should I feel bad, right?- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.25,0:15:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,只是因为你很喜欢他 我好奇而已\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's just because you like him so much, I'm wondering.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.46,0:15:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但你也喜欢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, but you do too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.37,0:15:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,但一个女人的确完成不了同样的事\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's true that a woman couldn't have done the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.50,0:15:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我也愿意有九个孩子\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I mean, I would like to have nine kids
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.97,0:15:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,跟五个不一样的男人\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}from five different men.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.80,0:15:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,那还不错\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}That's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.97,0:15:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's just I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.85,0:15:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢某种连贯性\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I like a certain coherence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.47,0:15:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢我爱的艺术家\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I don't like it when artists I love
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.64,0:15:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,在现实里德不配位\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}don't behave well in real life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.39,0:15:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,那你得到想要的答案了 克丽斯\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So you have your answer, Chris.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.77,0:15:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼在他的艺术和生活里都一样残忍\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Bergman was as cruel in his art as in his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.49,0:15:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.24,0:15:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.88,0:17:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我要出门一趟\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I'm off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.25,0:17:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 去哪 - 有一场座谈会\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Where?- Got a panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.26,0:17:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 想一起来吗 - 不\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Wanna come?- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.59,0:17:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不想看看伯格曼中心吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oh. Don't wanna see the Bergman Center?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.26,0:17:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我明天去看 - 好吧\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- I'll see it tomorrow. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.81,0:17:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,行吧\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.68,0:17:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,好运\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.27,0:20:37.32,effect,,0,0,0,,妈
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.73,0:20:39.82,effect,,0,0,0,,我会很高兴如果你能
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:45.12,effect,,0,0,0,,{\pos(962.333,663.667)}打回来告诉我琼怎么样了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.99,0:20:48.66,effect,,0,0,0,,谢了 拜
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.59,0:21:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗨 - 嗨\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Hey.- Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.64,0:21:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- 怎么样呢 - 挺好的 \N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- How did it go?- It was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.14,0:21:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,人都很好 在那里看 沉默 的感觉很棒\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}People were nice.It's great to see The Silence there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.56,0:21:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我说得有点多了 但\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I talked too much, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.77,0:21:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你想喝点茶吗 - 喝一点 当然 \N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- You want some tea?- I'd love some, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.87,0:21:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我想琼了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I miss June.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.24,0:21:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你妈妈发了段视频给我\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oh, I got a video from your mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.91,0:21:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我就没收到\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.62,0:21:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道 因为她最爱我吧\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I know, but that's because I'm her favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.21,0:21:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,看吧\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.90,0:21:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,傀儡生涯 很硬核的伯格曼片\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}From the Life of Marionettes,pretty hardcore Bergman there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.44,0:22:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,但那是部德国片\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, but it's a German one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.27,0:22:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我想看部瑞典片 比如一部夏天的电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I'd like to see a Swedish one.Like a summer film.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.03,0:22:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不要莫妮卡 - 对 莫妮卡 拜托\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Not Monika.- Yeah, Monika, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.32,0:22:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,不行 看过太多遍了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Nah, seen it too often.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.32,0:22:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- 排演之后 - 芬妮和亚历山大\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- After the Rehearsal?- Fanny and Alexander?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.37,0:22:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,一样的 这片我滚瓜烂熟了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Same thing.I know that one by heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.95,0:22:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,第七封印\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The Seventh Seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.37,0:22:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,不行 那部我受不了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}No, I can't stand that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.46,0:22:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,但那是他最出名的一部 我还没看过\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}But it's his most famous one, and I haven't seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.21,0:22:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- 豺狼时刻 - 不行 这片里\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Hour of the Wolf?- No, that's the one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.67,0:22:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,里面有个孩子的头撞石头上去了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}where a child's head gets bashed against a boulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.67,0:22:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,也对\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.25,0:22:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,不行 如果我们不看第七封印的话\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}No, if we don't see Seventh Seal,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.42,0:22:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,至少看部友善点的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}then at least a nice one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.88,0:22:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,可没这种东西\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}There's no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.39,0:22:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们下载部电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Then we download a film.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.97,0:22:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你想看珠穆朗玛峰吗 这部轻松多了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You wanted to see Everest. It's easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.97,0:22:32.39,comment,,0,0,0,,此处非伯格曼的电影 可能指的是同名纪录片
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.39,0:22:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 处女泉 - 我知道了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Source!- I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.60,0:22:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,萨拉邦德\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Saraband.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.31,0:22:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,对 萨拉邦德\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, Saraband.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.81,0:22:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那部我没有 - 操\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- I don't have that one.- Oh, fuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.02,0:22:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,不然我还有一个35毫米的拷贝 我们之前放的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Or else I have a 35mm print.We showed it earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.02,0:22:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,明天就要回斯德哥尔摩了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's going back to Stockholm tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.82,0:22:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么电影 - 呼喊与细语\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- What film?- Cries and Whispers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.53,0:22:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你想要一部友善点的伯格曼 - 唔\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- You wanted a nice Bergman.- Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.91,0:22:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你们可以随意坐\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Alright, you can sit anywhere you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.99,0:22:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但不能坐在第一排\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but not in that seat on the first row.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.91,0:22:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,得保持空置 因为那是伯格曼的座位\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It has to stay empty because it's Bergman's.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.04,0:23:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 可以吗 - 谢了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Right?- Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.25,0:24:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,就像一部未经宣泄的恐怖电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's a like a horror movie without catharsis.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.88,0:24:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你的观点是\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Your point being?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.71,0:24:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,通常来说 当你看完一部恐怖电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Well, usually when you come out of a horror movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.01,0:24:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得安心了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}you feel reassured
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.97,0:24:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你知道你刚看到的 不可能发生在你身上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}because you know what you just saw can't happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.10,0:24:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但呼喊与细语里不是这样\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Not with Cries and Whispers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.14,0:24:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,那种孤独 痛苦 对死亡的恐惧\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The solitude, the agony, the horror of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.27,0:24:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,都原封不动地在那里\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's the way things are.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.65,0:24:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不是 那只是一场梦\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}No, it's not. It's a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.85,0:24:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,会更像一场该死的噩梦\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Or more like a fucking nightmare.
