Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.15,0:33:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢 - 很高兴见到你\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Thank you.- Nice to have met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.41,0:33:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我有些苹果酒 当地的 很好喝\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I have some cider.It's local cider. It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.12,0:33:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,在后面 你能打开吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's in the back.Can you open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.92,0:33:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.59,0:33:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要去哪\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.97,0:33:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我想着从乌拉哈乌开始\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I was thinking Ullahau to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.10,0:33:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,乌拉哈乌\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Ullahau?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.48,0:33:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,大家好\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.27,0:33:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我想大家都到了 那么我们就能出发了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I think that we're all here, so we can get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.69,0:33:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫菲利西亚 很高兴能担当你们\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}My name is Felicia, and I'm happy to be your guide
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.15,0:33:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,一年一度伯格曼之旅的向导\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}for the annual Bergman Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.99,0:33:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我的两位同事 薇薇安和麦肯\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}My two colleagues,Vivianne and Majken,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.12,0:34:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,将会协助我\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}are going to help me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.45,0:34:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,今天天气很好 阳光晴朗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It is a nice, sunny day,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.20,0:34:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,更是锦上添花\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}which is a great plus.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.00,0:34:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,已经在手机上下载了软件的人\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}For those of you who downloaded the app on your iPhones,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.79,0:34:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,现在可以打开了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}now is the time to start it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.21,0:34:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以帮助你们 通过法罗的地图\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&} With it, you'll be able to follow our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.96,0:34:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,来跟上我们的游览\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}on the map of Faro.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.38,0:34:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,现在 你们可以上车了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Now, if you all come onto the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.67,0:34:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我还没有介绍你们 弗兰切斯科莫利纳 安东尼桑德斯\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I didn't introduce you earlier, Francisco Molina, Anthony Sanders.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.84,0:34:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你好吗 - 很荣幸\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- How do you do.- Pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.46,0:34:34.42,effect,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\pos(509,85)\c&HFFFFFF&}没什么特别的，帮我带点土豆和大蒜
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.46,0:34:34.42,effect,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\c&HFFFFFF&\pos(735.667,135.667)}谢
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.46,0:34:34.42,effect,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\c&HFFFFFF&\pos(617.267,186.867)}有你妈妈的消息吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.46,0:34:34.42,effect,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\c&H000000&\pos(214.067,234.867)}还没，我今早打电话给她
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.46,0:34:34.42,effect,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\c&HFFFFFF&\pos(681.267,273.267)\clip(560,220.8,604.8,297.6)\t(\clip(560,220.8,758.4,278.4))}你不来吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.60,0:34:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,弗兰切斯科在巴塞罗那大学教书\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Francisco teaches at University of Barcelona.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.60,0:34:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他不费吹灰之力赢下了昨晚的伯格曼竞赛\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And he was the hands-down winner of last night's Bergman Quiz.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.98,0:34:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 走吗 - 好\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Shall we?- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.00,0:34:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道 伯格曼并不喜欢那部电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You know, Bergman didn't like that movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.88,0:34:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是他们去意大利的原因\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, that's why they went to Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.88,0:34:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,里面有大量那些关于\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah. it's got all the stuff about
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.26,0:35:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,他的个人生活 婚姻的东西\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}his personal life, his marriages...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.64,0:35:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将经过伯格曼拍摄 犹在镜中 的地点\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}We're arriving at the spot where Bergman shot Through a Glass Darkly,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.60,0:35:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他因此探索了法罗岛\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}film which allowed him to discover Faro.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.02,0:35:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,一开始 伯格曼并不想在瑞典拍摄\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}At first, Bergman didn't want to shoot it in Sweden.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.27,0:35:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,他想去苏格兰外的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He wanted to go to the Orkney Islands
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.11,0:35:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,奥克尼群岛\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}off the Scottish coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.11,0:35:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但制片人认为那样太贵了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}But the producers thought that that would be far too expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.15,0:35:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 他们尝试着说服他在瑞典拍摄\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, they tried to persuade him to film it in Sweden instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.94,0:35:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,这个地方大概在1700年左右形成\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}This place came to be around 1700.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.94,0:35:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,人们开始砍伐树木\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}People started cutting down the trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.90,0:35:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,沙土就会从北面吹进来\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}and the sand would blow in from the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.98,0:35:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,在空地上创造出这些沙丘\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}creating these dunes in the clearings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.65,0:36:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,乌拉哈乌意思是 滚动的沙丘\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Ullahau means "the rolling dunes",
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.86,0:36:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,因为人们认为这意味着审判日将到来\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}because people thought this meant judgment day was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.95,0:36:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,他们曾经说\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And they used to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.42,0:36:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,意思是当乌拉哈乌与沙土在高处相接\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}which means that when Ullahau and sand high meet,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.88,0:36:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,审判日就近了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}judgment day is near.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.25,0:36:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,后来有个人新种了很多树\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And then a man planted many new trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.96,0:36:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,防止风沙吹入\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}stopping more sand from coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.47,0:36:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但这些沙丘已经形成 它们留了下来\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}But the dunes that were already here, they remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.86,0:36:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这让我想要去海滩\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}This makes me want to go to the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.20,0:36:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 没问题 - 一块舒适的沙滩\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- It's no problem.- A nice sandy beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.41,0:36:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,一共有两个 南滩和北滩\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}There is two of them, the north beach and the south beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.00,0:36:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,南滩面积大 浪也大\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The south beach is large, with big waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.04,0:36:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,游客更多\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's more touristy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.96,0:36:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,北滩没有游客 没有风 水很清\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The north has no tourists, no wind, the water is clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.92,0:37:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但有很多水母 - 不行\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- but lots of jellyfish.- No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.84,0:37:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们是无害的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, but they're harmless.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.09,0:37:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但南滩确实有一些会扎人\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And the south does have a few which are stingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.80,0:37:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,糟糕多了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Much, much worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.31,0:37:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,电影中的房子就在这\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, the house in the film was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.86,0:37:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上 它们只建了外墙 内景呢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Actually, they only built the facade and the interiors
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.19,0:37:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 大多是在摄影棚里拍的 - 房子后来怎么了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- were mostly shot in studio.- What happened to the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.24,0:37:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他们只能在拍摄后把它拆掉\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Well, they had to tear it down after the shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.62,0:37:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼当时在找一处有古树的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Bergman was looking for a small garden
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.58,0:37:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,小花园 这也是他部分选址这里的原因\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&} with old trees, and that's part of why he picked this spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.37,0:37:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,树都还在这里\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The trees are still here,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.33,0:37:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你也可以看到 他们拆除墙的地方\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}and you can also see where they took down the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.92,0:37:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,这里你能看到墙被替换过了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Here you can see that\ he wall has been replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.59,0:37:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,一直到 这里\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}All the way to, uh... here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.18,0:37:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 这些石头是不一样的 这些是他们用来\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, the stones are different. These are the ones they used
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.22,0:37:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,来重建墙壁的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}when they rebuilt the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.81,0:37:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你往那边看\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And, if you look over here,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.35,0:37:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以看到栈桥的遗址\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}you can see where the jetty once was built.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.65,0:38:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是栈桥的基座\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, that was like the foundation of the jetty.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.78,0:38:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这棵树也曾出现在电影中\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And, uh, this tree is actually also in the movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.95,0:38:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,但当时还是小树\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but it was really small then.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.95,0:38:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,现在已经长了很多\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, it has grown a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.58,0:38:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,因为电影差不多是六十年前拍的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}since the film was made about 60 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.12,0:38:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,当伯格曼到达法罗 有什么事发生了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}When Bergman arrived in Faro, something happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.21,0:38:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他一见钟情\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It was love at first sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.71,0:38:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼对这座岛的美丽目眩神迷\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Bergman was dazzled by the island's beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.34,0:38:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,如同他找到了属于自己的景致\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It was as if he had found his own landscape,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.05,0:38:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,那份景致早已存在于他心中\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}one that already existed inside of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.55,0:38:51.43,effect,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFFFFFF&\fs40\pos(96.2,78.6)}托尼
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.55,0:38:51.43,effect,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFFFF&\fs40\pos(310.6,126.6)}很高兴你在伯格曼之旅上放了我鸽子
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.50,0:38:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,在拍摄 假面 之前 伯格曼 伯格曼已经住院了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Before making Persona, Bergman had been hospitalized,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.67,0:39:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,同时受着精神和肉体上的折磨\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}suffering both mental and physical exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.29,0:39:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但在假面之后 他就变得从未有过的开心\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}But after Persona, he was as happy as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.01,0:39:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,假面 体现了他的转折和完善\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Persona incarnates this transition and this fullness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.01,0:39:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼从未忘过这点\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Bergman never forgot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.01,0:39:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他说 假面是那部拯救了他人生的电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}He said that Persona was the film that saved his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.53,0:39:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,羞耻 这部片的名字 是带冠词还是不带的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Is it Shame or The Shame?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.90,0:39:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,在瑞典语 它叫Skammen\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}In Swedish it's Skammen,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.57,0:39:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,意思即为 羞耻\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}which means "The Shame",
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.32,0:39:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,但英语标题是不带冠词的 我想\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but the English title is Shame, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.19,0:39:47.28,effect,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\c&H272D29&\b1\bord0.5\3c&H272D29&\frx0\fry358\frz346.1\fsp1\pos(1069,376.2)\be1}别生气 你的大师课一直在拖堂 晚点家里见 享受伯格曼之旅
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.87,0:39:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,奇怪 在英国它上映的时候是带冠词的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oddly enough, in the UK it was released as The Shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.42,0:39:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼知道他会收到很多批评\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Bergman knew that he would receive a lot of criticism
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.34,0:39:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他提起越南的方式\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}for evoking Vietnam in this manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.68,0:39:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,因为瑞典关于战争的辩论\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Because the debate in Sweden about the war
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.85,0:39:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,是非黑即白的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}was very black and white.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.35,0:39:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他的电影却十分地灰\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}His film is extremely gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.94,0:40:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到了吗 水母\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Did you see, jellyfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.56,0:40:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你想买一些羔羊皮吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Would you like to buy some lambskin?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.48,0:40:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Um... yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.78,0:40:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道怎么选\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I can't choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.82,0:40:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这些黑色长毛的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I prefer the black, long-haired ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.62,0:40:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但它们比较贵\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}But they're more expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.46,0:41:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,当然了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, totally.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.63,0:41:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,大家 大家\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, guys, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.21,0:41:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我们通常会在结束伯格曼导览的时候\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}We traditionally end the Bergman Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.30,0:41:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,吃一个羊肉汉堡\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}by having a lamb burger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.88,0:41:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都要吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Is everyone up for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.97,0:41:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不然你们也可以选素食汉堡 - 不\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Otherwise you can have a veggie burger.- No!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.01,0:41:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,由豺狼时刻 羞耻 安娜的热情 组成\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Comprising of Hour of the Wolf, Shame, The Passion of Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.85,0:41:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼本人不这么看\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Uh, you know, Bergman didn't see them that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.65,0:41:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但 你知道 他不认为\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, but, you know,he didn't consider
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.77,0:41:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,犹在镜中 沉默 冬日之光\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Through a Glass Darkly, The Silence, and Winter Light
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.19,0:41:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,是三部曲 但有的评论家把它们视为\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}as a trilogy, and yet, some critics still see them
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.69,0:41:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,关于信仰丧失的三部曲\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}as a trilogy about the loss of faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.44,0:41:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 他肯定说它们是三部曲了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I mean, he definitely said they were a trilogy,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.99,0:41:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,但又收回了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but then walked it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.49,0:41:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他说那是三部曲\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Just because he said it's a trilogy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.82,0:41:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,也不代表实质上就是\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}doesn't mean it is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.20,0:41:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.71,0:41:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你的汉普斯之旅\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Thank you for the Hampus Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.21,0:41:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,希望你喜欢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I hope you enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.46,0:41:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢极了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I loved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.01,0:41:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,别忘了你的羊皮\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Don't forget your sheepskins.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.73,0:42:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- 再见 - 拜\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- See you.- Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.62,0:42:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,很好看\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Très chic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.00,0:42:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,多谢你的支持\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Thanks for the support.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.34,0:42:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到巴士 有点被吓跑了 对不起\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I saw the bus and freaked out. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.76,0:42:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,没事\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}That's alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.93,0:42:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么样\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.18,0:42:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,挺好的 实际上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It was pretty good, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.81,0:42:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但我回来之后 觉得有点恶心\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}But I've been feeling a bit yuck since I got back.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.64,0:42:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- 为什么 怎么了 - 肯定是因为汉堡\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Why, what happened?- Must have been the burger.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.78,0:42:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 你去哪了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.74,0:42:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,开车转转\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Driving around.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.40,0:42:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,开车转转\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oh, yeah. driving around?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.74,0:43:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我遇到了一个男的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Mmm. I met a guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.82,0:43:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你遇到了一个男的 行\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oh, you met a guy? Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.33,0:43:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 一个学生 - 嗯嗯\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- A student.- Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.12,0:43:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- 一个学生 是吧 - 在斯德哥尔摩学电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- A student, was he?- A film student from Stockholm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.87,0:43:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,他帅吗 性感吗 是这样吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oh. Was he handsome, was he sexy, was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.29,0:43:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他在谈伯格曼的时候是不是精彩绝伦\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Was he brilliant when he talked about Bergman?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.71,0:43:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,不像你 但 他的笨拙也有他的魅力\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Not like you, but, um, his clumsiness had its charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.46,0:43:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 可以闭嘴了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oh, thanks. Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.26,0:45:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你在找什么吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Looking for something, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.39,0:45:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不 - 噢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- No.- Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.62,0:47:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 嗨\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Hey. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.37,0:47:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我在找一栋房子\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I'm looking for the house
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.67,0:47:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,犹在镜中 里的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}from Through a Glass Darkly.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.04,0:47:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼的电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Bergman's film.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.96,0:47:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思 不懂英语\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Sorry, don't understand English.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.17,0:47:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,英格玛伯格曼\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Ingmar Bergman?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.22,0:47:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,住在岛上的电影工作者\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The filmmaker who lived on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.43,0:47:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.52,0:47:40.52,effect,,0,0,0,,谢了
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.78,0:47:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,别啊\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oh, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.82,0:48:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你想吃午餐吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You want to have lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.03,0:48:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,恶心心\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.91,0:48:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我去看了 犹在镜中 里的房子\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I went to see the house from Through a Glass Darkly,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.25,0:48:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,但没找到\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but I couldn't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.75,0:48:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- 就没有 不存在的 - 什么\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- There isn't one. Never was.- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.21,0:48:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但地图上有幅图\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}But the picture on the map?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.17,0:48:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他们只建了外观 内部都是在摄影棚拍的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}They built the facade, and they shot the interiors in a studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.80,0:48:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼导览 宝贝\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Bergman Safari, babes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.39,0:48:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么样了 你写到哪了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}How's it going?Where you at?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.43,0:49:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,还在做大纲\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I'm still doing the outline,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.27,0:49:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不知道还想不想写下去\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but I don't know if I want to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.81,0:49:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不呢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.94,0:49:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我担心它会像我已经做过的东西\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Because I'm afraid it's like stuff I've already done.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.48,0:49:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不可能\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}No... not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.90,0:49:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为我们花上一辈子\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I thought we spent all whole lives
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.07,0:49:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,讲述同样的事物\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}saying the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.91,0:49:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是这样 从不同的角度\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}We do, but from different perspectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.83,0:49:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你得相信你自己\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You just gotta trust yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.79,0:49:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,角色 对白 环境 都对得上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Characters, the dialogues, the situations, it all fits,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.42,0:49:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,但有什么在拖着我无法前进\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but something is holding me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.01,0:49:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,有什么事在让我焦虑\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Something is making me anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.55,0:49:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,那就不一样了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Oh, well, that's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.22,0:49:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,如果它在让你焦虑 休息一下\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}If it's making you anxious, take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.51,0:49:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你刚刚才让我写 现在又让我别写\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You just said "write". Now you say "don't write".
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.02,0:49:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这于事无补 没那么简单\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}That doesn't help. It's not easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.94,0:49:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道写作对我来说有多困难\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You know how hard writing is for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.44,0:49:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,它是 是折磨\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's... it's torture.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.69,0:49:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,是自我引发的痛苦\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's self-inflicted agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.19,0:49:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,是不可能的任务\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's blood from a stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.73,0:49:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那 做点别的事\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Well, then, do something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.40,0:49:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,像什么呢 全职家庭主妇\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah, like what, full-time housewife?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.74,0:49:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个备受尊敬的职业\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Well, it's an honorable profession.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.46,0:50:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,没有理由说 写作对你来说会这么难\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You know, there's no reason writing has to be so difficult for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.88,0:50:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你不是十五岁了 你已经长大成人了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You're not 15. You've outgrown that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.84,0:50:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,可能我还没有 我也还是十五岁\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Well, maybe I am because I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.93,0:50:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,写点别的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Write something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.51,0:50:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,又不是说我有一箩筐的主意\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's not like I have a ton of projects
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.89,0:50:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,都堆在脑子里\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}lined up in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.52,0:50:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我真的以为你会鼓励我\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I really thought you would encourage me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.81,0:50:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我在努力\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I'm trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.60,0:50:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我喜欢你的作品\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You know I love your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.28,0:50:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,那你的怎么样了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}How's your thing going?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.53,0:50:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上 挺好的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Um, pretty good, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.07,0:50:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,关于什么的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}What's it about?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.58,0:50:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,关于\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's about, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.41,0:50:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,一些不可见的事物\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}how invisible things circulate
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.29,0:50:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,在一对情侣之间流动\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}within a couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.79,0:50:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,故事呢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And the story?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.38,0:50:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你什么都不跟我说呢 我什么都告诉你\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Why don't you ever tell me anything? I tell you everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.92,0:50:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不想话说得太早 - 噢\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Don't wanna jinx it.- Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.35,0:51:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你能告诉我在哪发生的吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Can you tell me where it takes place?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.18,0:51:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这里\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.39,0:51:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这里 法罗 - 对\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Here?! Faro?- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.48,0:51:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,别说得像我应该知道一样\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Don't say that like I'm supposed to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.40,0:51:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我以为你知道 - 我没有\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Well, I thought you did.- No, I don't,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.86,0:51:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你什么都不告诉我\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}because you don't tell me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.91,0:51:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我有个标题 - 嗯\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- I've got a title.- Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.12,0:51:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以自己留着\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You can keep it to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.69,0:51:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.24,0:51:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,是剧本的原因吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Is it your script?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.33,0:52:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,琼小姐 你想回家吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Miss June, you want to go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.34,0:52:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.35,0:53:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我能告诉你我在写什么吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Can I tell you about what I'm writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.94,0:53:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.36,0:53:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,是一段漫长故事的最后一节\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's the last episode of a longer story.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.03,0:53:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,可能太过单薄不适合拍成电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, maybe it's too flimsy and not enough for a movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.66,0:53:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但我还是想听你的意见- 好\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- but I would like your opinion.- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.41,0:53:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,故事发生在\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So it takes place
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.04,0:53:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,三天内 在一场婚礼上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}over three days at a wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.79,0:53:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我还没想好在哪里\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I don't know where yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.42,0:53:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,但可能是像这里的地方\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but maybe a place like here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.21,0:53:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,像法罗岛\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Like Faro.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.96,0:53:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,一个小岛 会有很好的效果\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}An island, actually, would work very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.01,0:53:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,开始的时候可以是在飞机上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Um, and it could start on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.47,0:53:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,或者是船上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Or maybe on a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.77,0:53:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 我们到了一艘波罗的海的游船上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, we're on a ferry in the Baltic Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.73,0:53:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,从本土到哥特兰岛\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}from the mainland to Gotland.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.90,0:53:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,四小时的航程 而当时是春天\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's a four-hour ride, and it's spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.03,0:54:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,或者是夏天\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Or maybe it should be summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.78,0:54:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,晚夏\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's late summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.11,0:54:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,一个年轻的女人遥望远方\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}A young woman looks into the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.07,0:54:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,她的名字是艾米\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Her name is Amy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.28,0:54:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,她差不多我的年纪 或者年轻一点\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}She's about my age or maybe a bit younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.87,0:54:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那就说她二十八吧\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Let's say she's 28.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.30,0:54:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,她是电影的主要角色\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}She's the main character of the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.59,0:54:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,那天早上 她从纽约到斯德哥尔摩\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}She arrived in Stockholm that morning from New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.39,0:54:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,来参加一个老朋友 妮可莱特的婚礼\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}She's come for the wedding of an old friend, Nicolette,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.68,0:54:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,她嫁给了一个叫约纳斯的瑞典人\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}who's marrying a Swede named Jonas.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.31,0:54:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,庆祝活动发生在哥特兰岛\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The celebration takes place on an island
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.10,0:54:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,北端的一个小岛\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}off the northern tip of Gotland.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.27,0:54:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,一个叫法罗的岛屿\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}An island called Faro.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.52,0:54:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这对艾米来说显然意义重大\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Which is hardly insignificant to Amy,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.03,0:54:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- 因为她是一个导演 - 对\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- as she's a director.- Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.40,0:54:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,伯格曼在她的想象中有着很重要的地位\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And Bergman occupies a very important place in her imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.99,0:54:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,对于许多人来说 他指向令人生畏的事物\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}For many, he's a formidable reference,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.87,0:54:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,但对她来说 他是\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but for her, he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.12,0:54:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,某种避难所 一种宽慰\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}sort of refuge, a consolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.04,0:54:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗯 - 但\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Mm-hmm.- And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.46,0:55:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这并不是她眼下所关心的事物\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}and yet it's not him she's thinking about right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.50,0:55:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,另一个人占据了她的大脑\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Another man is monopolizing her thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.47,0:55:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,他的名字是约瑟夫\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Joseph is his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.05,0:55:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,她放不下约瑟夫\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Joseph she can't let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.51,0:55:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米在十五岁遇见了约瑟夫 当时他十七\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Amy was 15 when she met Joseph, who was 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.02,0:55:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,他们充满激情而又尴尬地爱着彼此 像青少年一样\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}They loved each other passionately and awkwardly, like teenagers do.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.15,0:55:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他们害得对方粉身碎骨\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And they tore each other to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.65,0:55:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,约瑟夫在艾米18岁的时候离开了她\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Joseph left Amy the day she turned 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.78,0:55:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他们劳燕分飞\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}They each went their own ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.49,0:55:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,但艾米从未忘记约瑟夫\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but Amy never forgot Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.74,0:55:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们多年过后再见到彼此\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}When they saw each other again years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.29,0:55:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他们意识到对彼此的感觉仍未消散\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}they realized that their feelings were still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.16,0:55:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,对彼此的感觉依然难以抗拒\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The attraction was still overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.04,0:55:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他们变成了爱人\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}They became lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.42,0:55:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他们更成熟了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}They were more mature,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.38,0:55:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,更能理解对方\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}understood each other better,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.34,0:55:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但沧海桑田\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}but circumstances had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.63,0:55:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的生活里已没有给这段爱情的位置\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And there was no place in their lives for this love story anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.34,0:55:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次来得太早 第二次太迟\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The first time had been too soon, second too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.52,0:55:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 他们放弃了 彼此不再见面\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, they gave up and stopped seeing each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.85,0:56:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望这部电影会是\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I'd like this film to be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.56,0:56:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,会是他们故事的最后篇章\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}the last chapter of their story,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.48,0:56:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管是一连串的失败\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}which was just a series of failures
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.44,0:56:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,背叛和戏剧性\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}and betrayals and dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.53,0:56:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这个故事充满了不可能的悼念\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The story of impossible mourning,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.53,0:56:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,还有折磨 却在少数强烈\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}of suffering, overshadowed by a few memories
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.12,0:56:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,的快乐记忆中不值一提\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}of intense happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.62,0:56:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 听从妮可莱特的建议\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}So, following Nicolette's advice,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.83,0:56:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米与约纳斯的两个朋友碰面\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Amy met up with two of Jonas' friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.00,0:56:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他们从斯德哥尔摩乘车前往法罗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}They were going to Faro by car from Stockholm.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.21,0:56:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,约瑟夫也一样\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Joseph did the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.84,0:56:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管他从奥斯陆出发\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}though he started out from Oslo.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.34,0:56:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 在多年分离后\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And so, after several years apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.01,0:56:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,两位爱人发现他们\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}the two lovers find themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.60,0:56:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,一起坐在了陌生人\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}sitting in the back seat of a car
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.73,0:56:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,车辆的后座\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}driven by total strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.31,0:56:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,威尔玛和皮特不知道约瑟夫和艾米的过去\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Wilma and Peter don't know of Joseph's and Amy's past.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.19,0:56:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,心照不宣地 他们装傻了起来\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}By tacit agreement, they play dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.28,0:56:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,出于羞怯 或当作游戏\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Out of bashfulness, or as a game,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.28,0:56:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,他们假装不怎么了解对方\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}they pretend they vaguely know each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.66,0:56:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,装傻充愣只让艾米的欲望增加了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}This charade only increases Amy's desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.20,0:57:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你们在婚礼后 还会待在瑞典吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Will you be spending any time in Sweden after the wedding?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.08,0:57:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我要直接回去了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}No, I'm heading straight back.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.13,0:57:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我跟我女儿保证了 - 真甜 她多大\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- I promised my daughter.- Oh, sweet. How old?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.67,0:57:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 四岁 - 真好\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- She's four.- Gorgeous.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.51,0:57:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你呢 - 没有孩子\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- What about you?- No kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.22,0:57:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 你之后还要留在瑞典吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I mean, are you staying in Sweden after?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.76,0:57:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我得回去 实际上\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Ah! No, I have to go right back, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.81,0:57:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,使命在召唤\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Duty calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.48,0:57:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有为教堂准备一条领带 会有问题吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Is it a problem if I don't have a... a tie for church?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.98,0:57:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我本来要在机场买一条 结果忘了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I was going to buy one at the airport, but I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.82,0:57:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不 没事的 - 我也在想\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- No, it's fine...- I was also wondering,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.11,0:57:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我发现我准备穿的裙子 是白色的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&} I realized the dress I planned to wear, it's white.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.20,0:57:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是我唯一的好裙子 - 通常来说 只有新娘穿白色的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- It's my only nice dress.- Well, usually, only the bride wears white.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.83,0:57:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- 操 - 我是说 你得去问妮可莱特\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Shit.- I mean, you're gonna have to ask Nicolette.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.33,0:57:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- 她可能不会介意 - 实际上 我不知道算不算白色\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- She probably won't mind.- Actually, I don't know that it's really white.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.29,0:57:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,有点像米色 或者奶油色 有点浅褐色\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}It's more like off-white or cream, kind of beige.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.15,0:58:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你想去上层甲板吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You want to go to the upper deck?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.40,0:58:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我看了你的电影\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I saw your movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.15,0:58:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道那个家伙吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You know that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.19,0:58:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,哪个家伙\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Wait, which guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.65,0:58:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,就是那个演我的\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}The one who plays me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.53,0:58:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,他怎么了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.53,0:58:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我比他好多了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}I'm much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.99,0:59:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,真的吗 在什么方面\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Really? In what ways?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.41,0:59:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,在所有方面\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}n all departments.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.75,0:59:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,从身体条件上开始\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Physically, to start with.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.87,0:59:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,最重要的作为一个人 他是个混蛋\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}And most of all as a person. He's a... he's a prick.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.59,0:59:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,操 我还以为我把你理想化了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Damn. I thought I'd idealized you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.05,0:59:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,理想化\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Idealized?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.30,0:59:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 希望你在开玩笑\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Okay. I hope you're kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.85,0:59:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们有一次去了维斯比 - 嘘\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- We've been to Visby once.- Shh!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.31,0:59:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,去中世纪周\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}To the medieval week.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.52,0:59:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么 - 他们有个 中世纪主题周\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- What...- They have, like, a medieval-themed week
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.94,0:59:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- 在节日上 - 你去了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- where they...- You went to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.77,0:59:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 当然 - 你去作历史重演了吗\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Of course.- Did you do reenactments?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.77,0:59:32.94,comment,,0,0,0,,指对旧事件进行一次新的演绎 经常指戏剧里的表演 比如对历史战役的重现
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.94,0:59:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,算有\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Kind of.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.65,0:59:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,什么意思\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.36,0:59:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,信天翁镇 我们到了\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Albatross.We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.46,0:59:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,约纳斯\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Jonas?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.17,0:59:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,妮可莱特\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Nicolette?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.55,0:59:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 约纳斯 - 妮可莱特\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Jonas?- Nicolette?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.18,0:59:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,妮可莱特\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}Nicolette?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.93,1:00:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能看见我的裙子\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}You can't see my dress!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.60,1:00:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对不起 - 真的么\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}- Okay, sorry.- Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.77,1:00:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我发现她在穿裙子\N{\fs35\1c&H62A8EB&}We found her in the dress.
